      <h2 xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <span class="mw-headline" id="Stage_adaptation">Stage adaptation</span></h2>
      <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">A stage version of the musical has been adapted by <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ken_Ludwig" title="Ken Ludwig">Ken Ludwig</a>, and began previews at the <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alley_Theatre" title="Alley Theatre">Alley Theatre</a> (<a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Houston" title="Houston">Houston</a>) on April 29, 2008, officially opening on May 18 through June 22. The production, directed by Alley artistic director Gregory Boyd with choreography by Randy Skinner, stars <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harry_Groener" title="Harry Groener">Harry Groener</a> and Kerry O'Malley. The musical has many of the film's original songs, and also incorporates other Gershwin songs, such as "They All Laughed", "Let's Call the Whole Thing Off" and "Love Walked In".</p>
